wikidata-schema.dialog-explanation: The schema alignment skeleton below specifies how your tabular data will be transformed into Wikibase statements. You can drag and drop columns in statements: they will be replaced by their values once you export the statements.
wikidata-schema.invalid-schema-warning-issues: Your schema is incomplete, fix it to see the issues.
wikidata-schema.invalid-schema-warning-qs: Your schema is incomplete, fix it to see the preview.

new-item-created.title: This batch will create new Wikidata items.
new-item-created.body: Please make sure that these items do not exist yet and are suitable for inclusion in Wikidata.

new-item-without-labels-or-aliases.title: Some new items will be created without any label or alias.
new-item-without-labels-or-aliases.body: You should at least provide one label, so that others can understand what the item is about.

new-item-without-descriptions.title: Some new items will be created without any description.
new-item-without-descriptions.body: Adding descriptions will make it easier to disambiguate them from namesakes.

new-item-with-deleted-statements.title: You are trying to delete statements on new items.
new-item-with-deleted-statements.body: There is probably something wrong in your schema or project.

new-item-without-P31-or-P279.title: Some new items will be created without any type.
new-item-without-P31-or-P279.body: You should provide an "instance of" (P31) or "subclass of" (P279) statement for each item that you create.

statement-without-reference.title: Some statements are not referenced.
statement-without-reference.body: Please provide references for the statements that you add.
